# MidiParser

## Purpose

The **MidiParser** module is responsible for receiving and processing MIDI messages.

Its task is to read incoming MIDI data and provide the decoded message information to the main program.

---

## Description

MidiParser uses the standard Arduino MIDI Library.

The module receives MIDI messages, determines their type and provides access to the message type and note number.

The module does not control the keyboard and does not communicate with the shift registers.

---

## Public Interface

The module provides functions for:

* initializing the MIDI interface;
* receiving MIDI messages;
* checking for new messages;
* obtaining the MIDI message type;
* obtaining the note number.

---

## Operating Principle

During each iteration of the main program loop, the module checks whether a new MIDI message has been received.

If a message is available, its type and note number become available for further processing by the main program.

---

## Limitations

Version 1.0 supports:

* MIDI **Note On** messages;
* MIDI **Note Off** messages;
* a single MIDI channel.

Other MIDI message types are not processed in this version.

